WEBVTT

1
00:01:04.600 --> 00:01:05.870
My eyes!

2
00:01:06.240 --> 00:01:08.620
Medic! Someone get me a medic!

3
00:01:08.620 --> 00:01:11.680
It's no good! The reinforcements are
just a random group of mages!

4
00:01:30.510 --> 00:01:31.810
A mage?

5
00:01:36.670 --> 00:01:38.390
What are you doing. Visha?

6
00:01:40.690 --> 00:01:42.370
We can't provide air support anymore!

7
00:01:42.780 --> 00:01:44.650
<i>What are the platoon commander's orders?</i>

8
00:01:44.990 --> 00:01:47.750
Sh-She cannot allow us to retreat.

9
00:01:47.750 --> 00:01:50.830
We are to continue delaying
the enemy till the end.

10
00:01:58.480 --> 00:02:02.050
Believers. have faith in the Lord's blessings.

11
00:02:02.900 --> 00:02:05.520
For the Lord will not abandon us.

12
00:02:07.960 --> 00:02:13.650
Give me the power to destroy
the enemies of the Fatherland.

13
00:02:25.510 --> 00:02:28.440
An explosion spell...

14
00:02:31.030 --> 00:02:33.530
If you have time for idle chatter.

15
00:02:33.530 --> 00:02:36.050
spend it doing all you can to survive.

16
00:02:40.700 --> 00:02:42.220
Platoon Commander?

17
00:02:42.560 --> 00:02:44.580
We are soldiers.

18
00:02:44.580 --> 00:02:48.020
If the brass tells us to
do something. we do it.

19
00:02:54.620 --> 00:02:56.650
<i>Second Lieutenant Tanya Degurechaff.</i>

20
00:02:57.410 --> 00:03:00.130
<i>Amidst the downpour of shells and bullets.</i>

21
00:03:00.130 --> 00:03:02.650
<i>she flew high and nobly.</i>

22
00:03:04.110 --> 00:03:06.670
<i>Like a fairy of the battlefield.</i>

23
00:03:15.330 --> 00:03:18.310
<i>In a cursed world.
always engulfed in the flames of war.</i>

24
00:03:18.310 --> 00:03:21.220
<i>there was a nation known as the Empire.</i>

25
00:03:22.260 --> 00:03:28.710
<i>Its vast military and industrial power
made it virtually synonymous with victory.</i>

26
00:03:29.260 --> 00:03:33.700
<i>It possessed a large number of
brilliant military minds and mages.</i>

27
00:03:34.100 --> 00:03:39.090
<i>but it was surrounded on all sides
by strong potential enemies.</i>

28
00:03:40.200 --> 00:03:45.960
<i>For this reason.
its military formulated Plan 315.</i>

29
00:03:46.480 --> 00:03:50.180
<i>wherein border forces carried out
delaying actions in all theaters.</i>

30
00:03:50.180 --> 00:03:53.750
<i>buying time for a highly mobile.
concentrated main force to travel</i>

31
00:03:53.750 --> 00:03:56.110
<i>to each area and defeat the enemy there.</i>

32
00:03:56.110 --> 00:03:57.840
<i>At least. that was the plan.</i>

33
00:04:00.000 --> 00:04:05.170
Unified Year 1924. Imperial Capital Berun

34
00:04:05.310 --> 00:04:08.310
Imperial Strategic Headquarters

35
00:04:14.080 --> 00:04:16.230
What is the situation in the Rhine theater?

36
00:04:16.710 --> 00:04:19.350
When will the main force be deployed there?

37
00:04:18.650 --> 00:04:24.410
Vice Director of Strategy and Operations
Lieutenant Colonel Erich von Rerugen

38
00:04:20.530 --> 00:04:24.410
Movement from the northern areas
is being delayed.

39
00:04:24.580 --> 00:04:37.380
Deputy of Strategy and Operations
Brigadier General Kurt von Rudersdorf

40
00:04:24.980 --> 00:04:27.720
We must adjust the rail and ship schedules.

41
00:04:27.720 --> 00:04:30.540
so the deployment
will take another two weeks.

42
00:04:32.060 --> 00:04:34.410
We must pull back the lines even more?

43
00:04:34.670 --> 00:04:37.380
The western industrial areas
will be endangered.

44
00:04:37.660 --> 00:04:42.300
We don't even have enough reserves
to send reinforcements.

45
00:04:43.050 --> 00:04:45.530
We've been caught totally off-guard.

46
00:04:46.760 --> 00:04:51.460
From the start. a major offensive against
the Entente Alliance was a mistake!

47
00:04:52.160 --> 00:04:55.690
If we'd kept ourselves to
a limited mobilization...

48
00:04:59.020 --> 00:05:02.510
We were the ones who failed to convince

49
00:05:02.510 --> 00:05:07.980
the higher-ups that they were wrong
about the Republic's not mobilizing.

50
00:05:07.950 --> 00:05:19.120
Vice Director of Strategy and Operations
Brigadier General Hans von Zettour

51
00:05:08.660 --> 00:05:12.310
Plan 315 is no longer viable.

52
00:05:13.120 --> 00:05:15.950
Since our attempts to delay
the enemy aren't working.

53
00:05:15.950 --> 00:05:19.160
we'll have to move to a mobile defense. right?

54
00:05:19.160 --> 00:05:22.830
But that will be difficult.
given the state of the Rhine theater.

55
00:05:23.400 --> 00:05:26.910
Our forces are depleted and exhausted.
so it's beyond their capacity.

56
00:05:26.910 --> 00:05:32.440
We've already grabbed every
spare soldier we could to send there.

57
00:05:32.880 --> 00:05:35.350
That will buy some time.

58
00:05:36.080 --> 00:05:40.010
I suppose it helps to have
a talented contemporary. huh?

59
00:05:40.630 --> 00:05:43.630
Isn't that statement premature?

60
00:05:43.630 --> 00:05:44.360
What?

61
00:05:44.940 --> 00:05:49.510
Reports say we've lost over half
the units we've deployed.

62
00:05:50.070 --> 00:05:53.780
They say the Rhine theater
is now a living hell.

63
00:06:22.280 --> 00:06:27.780
Imperial Army 205th 
Assault Mage Company Platoon 3 Commander
Second Lieutenant Tanya Degurechaff

64
00:06:22.540 --> 00:06:24.880
Enemies sighted on the ground. two o'clock.

65
00:06:24.880 --> 00:06:26.310
Artillery spell.

66
00:06:27.030 --> 00:06:27.640
Fire!

67
00:06:27.640 --> 00:06:28.910
R-Right!

68
00:06:27.780 --> 00:06:31.900
Platoon 3 Member
Corporal Viktoriya Serebryakov

69
00:06:32.640 --> 00:06:33.800
It's coming from above!

70
00:06:33.800 --> 00:06:34.950
Damn the bastards!

71
00:06:36.200 --> 00:06:37.830
Die! Die!

72
00:06:37.920 --> 00:06:39.880
Platoon 3 Member
Corporal Harald von Vist

73
00:06:38.270 --> 00:06:39.990
Take this...

74
00:06:39.980 --> 00:06:42.480
You Republican bastards!

75
00:06:40.460 --> 00:06:42.510
Platoon 3 Member
Corporal Kurst von Walhorf

76
00:06:47.640 --> 00:06:49.150
Artillery...

77
00:06:49.150 --> 00:06:50.930
Take out the artillery.

78
00:06:50.930 --> 00:06:52.390
Come with me. Harald!

79
00:06:52.390 --> 00:06:53.170
Roger!

80
00:06:53.170 --> 00:06:55.800
Both of you corporals. get back here.

81
00:06:55.800 --> 00:06:59.340
Our mission is to delay the enemy
via flanking attacks.

82
00:06:59.340 --> 00:07:00.740
<i>Let us go. please.</i>

83
00:07:00.740 --> 00:07:02.210
<i>Now's our chance!</i>

84
00:07:02.210 --> 00:07:03.530
Your chance to what?

85
00:07:03.530 --> 00:07:04.560
Get back here!

86
00:07:04.560 --> 00:07:05.820
This is an order!

87
00:07:05.820 --> 00:07:07.440
<i>Take this!</i>

88
00:07:08.450 --> 00:07:09.760
<i>All right!</i>

89
00:07:09.760 --> 00:07:11.410
<i>Did you see that. Commander?</i>

90
00:07:11.410 --> 00:07:14.360
<i>We'll keep going and crush the artillery!</i>

91
00:07:33.120 --> 00:07:35.590
Too tired to eat. huh?

92
00:07:35.590 --> 00:07:37.130
Force it down if you have to.

93
00:07:37.130 --> 00:07:38.300
You won't last otherwise.

94
00:07:44.900 --> 00:07:49.900
They say the 202nd and 203rd Companies
were wiped out.

95
00:07:50.690 --> 00:07:53.460
I volunteered to come to the front lines.

96
00:07:54.260 --> 00:07:57.720
And now I've gotta work for that lieutenant?

97
00:07:57.720 --> 00:07:59.570
Platoon 3. of the 205th.

98
00:08:00.390 --> 00:08:02.130
Your captain is calling you.

99
00:08:04.470 --> 00:08:06.590
We're being sent back home?

100
00:08:06.590 --> 00:08:09.090
I would say you're getting off lightly.

101
00:08:09.090 --> 00:08:10.840
Be grateful.

102
00:08:11.530 --> 00:08:15.300
The army has no need for officer candidates
who disobey orders.

103
00:08:15.910 --> 00:08:18.040
But we were trying to take out the artillery!

104
00:08:18.590 --> 00:08:21.690
You know how many of our infantry
they took out. don't you?

105
00:08:21.690 --> 00:08:23.800
Is that all you have to say?

106
00:08:24.180 --> 00:08:25.910
An army is an organization.

107
00:08:25.910 --> 00:08:28.130
And organizations are nothing without rules!

108
00:08:28.130 --> 00:08:29.200
Dismissed.

109
00:08:32.710 --> 00:08:34.760
I... I refuse to accept this!

110
00:08:36.730 --> 00:08:39.970
I volunteered to come to the front lines!

111
00:08:39.970 --> 00:08:43.670
My only choices are victory or death!

112
00:08:44.110 --> 00:08:44.830
Me. too.

113
00:08:45.230 --> 00:08:47.590
I agree with Corporal Kurst.

114
00:08:47.590 --> 00:08:50.580
A man of the Empire is expected to be brave!

115
00:08:51.740 --> 00:08:57.720
Then you're saying you'll disobey
your superior officer's orders again?!

116
00:08:57.720 --> 00:08:58.300
Lieutenant!

117
00:09:06.280 --> 00:09:08.820
I'll take your opinion under advisement.

118
00:09:09.580 --> 00:09:13.190
But you'd best be prepared
to face some punishment.

119
00:09:38.360 --> 00:09:39.840
Corporal Serebryakov.

120
00:09:40.130 --> 00:09:42.380
Imperial Army 
205th Assault Mage Company Commander
First Lieutenant Ihlen Schwarzkopf

121
00:09:40.660 --> 00:09:42.300
is something wrong?

122
00:09:42.300 --> 00:09:44.990
Sch... Lieutenant Schwarzkopf!

123
00:09:45.630 --> 00:09:49.690
Um. I don't see Corporal Kurst
or Corporal Harald.

124
00:09:49.690 --> 00:09:50.860
That's right.

125
00:09:50.860 --> 00:09:52.930
You were in their class. weren't you?

126
00:09:52.930 --> 00:09:56.110
They've been transferred
to the rear as of today.

127
00:09:56.110 --> 00:09:58.710
To the rear?

128
00:09:58.710 --> 00:09:59.370
Yeah.

129
00:09:59.910 --> 00:10:03.980
They must be standing by in a pillbox now.

130
00:10:04.790 --> 00:10:08.800
This was at the suggestion of
Lieutenant Degurechaff.

131
00:10:09.590 --> 00:10:12.600
I heard they made her angry.

132
00:10:12.600 --> 00:10:13.540
Y-Yes.

133
00:10:13.930 --> 00:10:17.890
I was sure they'd be harshly punished...

134
00:10:20.640 --> 00:10:21.810
I see.

135
00:10:23.110 --> 00:10:25.950
They're being sent to the rear.
where it's safe.

136
00:11:03.350 --> 00:11:06.940
If you're wearing that uniform.
contribute to your country.

137
00:11:06.940 --> 00:11:10.390
The Empire doesn't have resources
to waste on weak soldiers.

138
00:11:10.390 --> 00:11:12.190
R-Right.

139
00:11:13.130 --> 00:11:14.890
Corporal Serebryakov!

140
00:11:14.890 --> 00:11:15.400
Yes?

141
00:11:16.070 --> 00:11:17.340
Call an emergency meeting.

142
00:11:20.450 --> 00:11:23.950
Bad news. everyone.

143
00:11:24.330 --> 00:11:27.290
Our 403rd Mage Company suddenly encountered

144
00:11:27.290 --> 00:11:30.280
and entered combat with
two companies of enemy mages.

145
00:11:31.060 --> 00:11:34.870
And they can't use artillery because
the observer mages were targeted.

146
00:11:34.870 --> 00:11:37.050
meaning they can no longer spot the shells.

147
00:11:37.750 --> 00:11:39.790
Enemy observer-hunters?

148
00:11:39.790 --> 00:11:41.030
Oh. right.

149
00:11:41.030 --> 00:11:44.790
You've encountered them in the north.
Lieutenant Degurechaff.

150
00:11:44.790 --> 00:11:46.850
And I never want to go through that again.

151
00:11:47.290 --> 00:11:51.860
We will leave immediately
to rescue the observers.

152
00:11:51.860 --> 00:11:53.230
Any questions?

153
00:11:54.860 --> 00:11:56.720
We can perform a delaying action.

154
00:11:56.720 --> 00:11:58.990
but rescuing them will be difficult.

155
00:11:59.990 --> 00:12:02.910
Even with that Type-95?

156
00:12:02.910 --> 00:12:06.740
I can still fight.
but Corporal Serebryakov is at her limit.

157
00:12:08.030 --> 00:12:12.790
I don't want to be the kind of incompetent
who goes to rescue someone.

158
00:12:12.790 --> 00:12:14.500
only to lose them and her soldier.

159
00:12:15.870 --> 00:12:18.290
Company Commander. I volunteer for this!

160
00:12:18.670 --> 00:12:21.120
I volunteer for the rescue mission!

161
00:12:21.420 --> 00:12:22.490
Stop.

162
00:12:22.490 --> 00:12:23.630
You can't do it.

163
00:12:23.970 --> 00:12:27.400
I-I'm an Imperial soldier. too.

164
00:12:27.400 --> 00:12:30.130
I'm certain I can complete the mission!

165
00:12:30.130 --> 00:12:31.010
Corporal!

166
00:12:31.010 --> 00:12:32.620
Company Commander!

167
00:12:32.620 --> 00:12:35.540
Please. please let me go!

168
00:12:36.810 --> 00:12:38.650
You heard her. Second Lieutenant.

169
00:12:38.650 --> 00:12:42.570
I understand your concerns.
but she says she's all right.

170
00:12:43.660 --> 00:12:45.590
Roger.

171
00:12:45.590 --> 00:12:48.320
I'll do the best I can.

172
00:12:51.070 --> 00:12:52.580
Lieutenant Degurechaff!

173
00:12:55.450 --> 00:12:57.040
Thank you.

174
00:12:57.040 --> 00:12:58.090
Corporal.

175
00:12:58.440 --> 00:13:00.830
you're really ready for this. right?

176
00:13:01.440 --> 00:13:02.330
Yes. ma'am.

177
00:13:03.030 --> 00:13:04.530
Understood.

178
00:13:04.530 --> 00:13:06.470
Time for work. then.

179
00:13:12.650 --> 00:13:13.380
Right!

180
00:13:26.430 --> 00:13:29.410
Command Post. this is Bravo 01.

181
00:13:29.410 --> 00:13:34.270
Enemy mages are stopping us
from artillery spotting!

182
00:13:34.270 --> 00:13:36.260
How much longer will reinforcements take?

183
00:13:37.520 --> 00:13:39.810
<i>Command Post to Bravo 01.</i>

184
00:13:39.810 --> 00:13:42.540
<i>The 205th Mage Company is en route.</i>

185
00:13:42.540 --> 00:13:46.260
<i>403rd Mage Company. continue spotting.</i>

186
00:13:47.090 --> 00:13:47.880
Damn it!

187
00:13:47.880 --> 00:13:50.850
Don't they understand what's going on?!

188
00:14:01.700 --> 00:14:04.320
Republican Army 106th Recon Mage Company

189
00:14:04.450 --> 00:14:08.200
Republican Army 
106th Recon Mage Company Commander
First Lieutenant Augustin Hosman

190
00:14:05.700 --> 00:14:08.550
I'd heard the Imperial mages were good.

191
00:14:08.550 --> 00:14:10.740
Guess you can't trust rumors...

192
00:14:11.140 --> 00:14:14.660
Troops. find the remaining observers!

193
00:14:15.400 --> 00:14:20.290
I've been trying. but they appear
to be hiding in the trenches.

194
00:14:20.290 --> 00:14:23.940
Then blow away anywhere
you think they might be.

195
00:14:23.940 --> 00:14:28.870
But a wide-area explosion spell
will drain our magic.

196
00:14:28.870 --> 00:14:29.720
It doesn't matter.

197
00:14:29.720 --> 00:14:31.620
Maximum firepower.

198
00:14:40.350 --> 00:14:44.200
"A-Attention. all units.
We've lost contact with friendly observers."

199
00:14:44.200 --> 00:14:46.210
What a mess.

200
00:14:46.210 --> 00:14:47.980
Sh-Should we turn back?

201
00:14:47.980 --> 00:14:50.800
No. it's a shame we weren't in time.

202
00:14:50.800 --> 00:14:52.700
but we're inside enemy firing range.

203
00:14:53.110 --> 00:14:55.910
We've gotta earn our pay.

204
00:14:56.160 --> 00:14:58.890
W-We only have one platoon.

205
00:14:58.890 --> 00:15:01.290
We can't fight a whole company.

206
00:15:01.290 --> 00:15:04.860
You said you were ready for this.

207
00:15:06.060 --> 00:15:09.580
Our enemy is on an exhausting.
long-range mission.

208
00:15:09.580 --> 00:15:14.040
And they've used a lot of firepower
to take out our observers.

209
00:15:14.040 --> 00:15:15.680
There's a good chance we can win.

210
00:15:18.140 --> 00:15:23.030
<i>But I guess losing new troops already
would hurt my promotion chances.</i>

211
00:15:24.880 --> 00:15:28.870
You are to rendezvous with
Lieutenant Schwarzkopf and provide support.

212
00:15:28.870 --> 00:15:31.890
I'll go ahead and destroy three platoons.

213
00:15:31.890 --> 00:15:34.450
The rest are yours.

214
00:15:34.450 --> 00:15:38.040
Man. it's rough being a salaryman.

215
00:15:38.040 --> 00:15:39.700
S-Salary...?

216
00:15:40.860 --> 00:15:43.210
I pray unto God.

217
00:15:43.210 --> 00:15:46.220
Lord. save my Fatherland.

218
00:15:53.230 --> 00:15:56.810
Magical signature. probably hostile.
approaching at high speed.

219
00:15:56.810 --> 00:15:58.890
Visual confirmation on enemy target.

220
00:15:58.890 --> 00:16:00.180
Distance. 2.000 meters.

221
00:16:00.180 --> 00:16:02.780
1.800... 1.600...

222
00:16:02.780 --> 00:16:03.390
She's fast!

223
00:16:04.070 --> 00:16:05.390
They've gone mad. huh?

224
00:16:05.900 --> 00:16:07.520
Prepare to intercept!

225
00:16:07.520 --> 00:16:08.750
Fire!

226
00:16:19.290 --> 00:16:20.620
What are you doing?

227
00:16:26.170 --> 00:16:28.540
Unable to maintain flight spell!
Leaving the battlefield!

228
00:16:26.520 --> 00:16:29.090
Scatter and climb!

229
00:16:29.090 --> 00:16:30.630
Get as high as you can!

230
00:16:32.010 --> 00:16:33.250
Commander!

231
00:16:53.280 --> 00:16:54.550
Damn it.

232
00:16:54.550 --> 00:16:56.030
Payback for Sean!

233
00:17:16.230 --> 00:17:18.350
How high up is she going?

234
00:17:19.180 --> 00:17:21.220
Commander. this is our max altitude.

235
00:17:28.180 --> 00:17:29.610
Impossible.

236
00:17:29.610 --> 00:17:32.220
She's over 10.000 meters in the air.

237
00:17:47.420 --> 00:17:48.380
Attention.

238
00:17:48.960 --> 00:17:52.370
<i>You are trespassing on Imperial territory.</i>

239
00:17:52.370 --> 00:17:53.980
An open comms channel?

240
00:17:53.980 --> 00:17:55.440
And this voice...

241
00:17:55.440 --> 00:17:57.130
So she is just a kid?

242
00:17:57.420 --> 00:18:00.130
This is our sky!

243
00:18:00.130 --> 00:18:01.920
Our home!

244
00:18:02.490 --> 00:18:05.290
<i>If you would stand against the Empire.</i>

245
00:18:05.290 --> 00:18:07.580
<i>we shall eliminate you without mercy.</i>

246
00:18:07.580 --> 00:18:09.520
<i>This is our task!</i>

247
00:18:09.850 --> 00:18:12.530
What an amazing patriot she is.

248
00:18:12.880 --> 00:18:14.060
Answer me!

249
00:18:14.470 --> 00:18:20.030
Why do you invade the Empire.
our homeland?

250
00:18:20.310 --> 00:18:21.930
If you want to play more.

251
00:18:21.930 --> 00:18:24.050
I'll give you some lead toys!

252
00:18:24.050 --> 00:18:25.200
Fire!

253
00:18:26.870 --> 00:18:28.070
A decoy.

254
00:18:31.400 --> 00:18:33.250
No room to negotiate. huh?

255
00:18:33.250 --> 00:18:35.170
You bitch!

256
00:18:47.180 --> 00:18:48.870
Spatial coordinates identified.

257
00:18:48.870 --> 00:18:51.480
Calculating stochastic evasion routes
for all targets.

258
00:18:52.430 --> 00:18:54.790
Magical energy in chamber
within normal parameters.

259
00:18:56.220 --> 00:18:59.280
<i>Attention. all allies. Prepare for impact.</i>

260
00:19:10.850 --> 00:19:17.000
Oh. Lord... Save our Fatherland
from these faithless invaders.

261
00:19:20.090 --> 00:19:22.010
At the end of our long road.

262
00:19:22.600 --> 00:19:26.040
we shall reach the promised land!

263
00:19:29.320 --> 00:19:30.770
Detecting massive magical signature!

264
00:19:37.190 --> 00:19:38.880
Is she the devil?

265
00:19:53.970 --> 00:19:56.360
A diffusive magical explosion.

266
00:19:56.360 --> 00:19:59.880
caused when magic under maximum pressure
mixes with the surrounding air.

267
00:20:00.510 --> 00:20:02.630
Even if you dodge the impact.

268
00:20:02.630 --> 00:20:06.380
you can't escape the oxygen deprivation
or carbon monoxide poisoning that follows.

269
00:20:07.840 --> 00:20:10.170
We didn't need to provide any support.

270
00:20:12.600 --> 00:20:14.660
In this cruel world of wars.

271
00:20:14.660 --> 00:20:17.640
there's no mage you can count on like her.

272
00:20:23.740 --> 00:20:25.870
The battle is over.

273
00:20:26.510 --> 00:20:30.720
Surrender now. and we'll guarantee
your rights as prisoners

274
00:20:30.720 --> 00:20:33.120
under the Treaty of Worms.

275
00:20:48.060 --> 00:20:51.900
Republican Capital Parisee

276
00:20:52.020 --> 00:20:54.110
Ministry of Defense

277
00:20:54.710 --> 00:20:58.030
This is the record of a computation jewel.

278
00:20:56.820 --> 00:21:00.160
Republic Army 2nd Mage Company
Lieutenant Colonel Severin Bientot

279
00:20:58.030 --> 00:21:00.100
which was recovered after a certain battle.

280
00:21:00.920 --> 00:21:06.600
This single mage wiped out the 106th Company.

281
00:21:07.470 --> 00:21:11.420
Her appearance was first confirmed
two months ago.

282
00:21:11.420 --> 00:21:14.030
She's a named mage
whose background is unclear.

283
00:21:14.030 --> 00:21:16.360
but our soldiers call her...

284
00:21:18.280 --> 00:21:20.620
"The Devil of the Rhine"?

285
00:21:24.840 --> 00:21:30.070
Redeployment of our central forces
to the Rhine has been completed.

286
00:21:30.740 --> 00:21:32.750
So we somehow made it in time.

287
00:21:33.360 --> 00:21:36.010
We put pretty heavy demands on you. huh?

288
00:21:36.010 --> 00:21:37.400
Don't worry about it.

289
00:21:37.400 --> 00:21:39.730
It's all for our country's sake.

290
00:21:39.730 --> 00:21:41.170
I must thank you somehow.

291
00:21:41.170 --> 00:21:43.760
How about one of my best bottles of wine?

292
00:21:44.200 --> 00:21:47.880
I'm afraid I've put off drinking
until our victory.

293
00:21:48.440 --> 00:21:49.600
Stubborn...

294
00:21:55.820 --> 00:21:57.230
Lieutenant Colonel Rerugen.

295
00:21:57.230 --> 00:21:59.280
is something wrong?

296
00:21:59.670 --> 00:22:01.440
No. it's just...

297
00:22:01.850 --> 00:22:03.190
Just what?

298
00:22:03.730 --> 00:22:07.180
W-Well. this report says

299
00:22:07.180 --> 00:22:11.800
that Second Lieutenant Tanya Degurechaff
was sent to the Rhine theater.

300
00:22:13.770 --> 00:22:16.300
Kurst and Harald are dead?

301
00:22:16.760 --> 00:22:21.040
While they were on standby.
an enemy shell struck their pillbox.

302
00:22:21.810 --> 00:22:23.300
It's a shame.

303
00:22:23.300 --> 00:22:24.700
No.

304
00:22:25.510 --> 00:22:28.070
Does the platoon commander know?

305
00:22:28.590 --> 00:22:30.620
No. probably not yet.

306
00:22:32.810 --> 00:22:34.750
The one called "White Silver"?

307
00:22:34.750 --> 00:22:37.650
The one who was awarded
the Silver Wings Assault Badge?

308
00:22:37.650 --> 00:22:40.680
It's surprising to see an ace at her age.

309
00:22:40.680 --> 00:22:42.910
What about her?

310
00:22:43.610 --> 00:22:49.340
I once had the opportunity to
see Lieutenant Degurechaff.

311
00:22:50.580 --> 00:22:51.590
Excuse me.

312
00:22:52.290 --> 00:22:55.090
There's something I want to report.

313
00:22:55.370 --> 00:22:56.370
What is it?

314
00:22:56.750 --> 00:23:00.610
Corporals Kurst and Harald—

315
00:23:00.610 --> 00:23:01.590
They're dead?

316
00:23:01.590 --> 00:23:03.600
Wh-Where did you learn that?

317
00:23:03.910 --> 00:23:06.140
It's self-evident.

318
00:23:06.140 --> 00:23:10.200
A pillbox doesn't move.
It's an ideal target for artillery.

319
00:23:10.840 --> 00:23:13.230
A perfect place for men who wanted to die.

320
00:23:15.200 --> 00:23:20.470
If I may be so forward as
to give you my opinion.

321
00:23:20.740 --> 00:23:26.880
You didn't know this would happen. did you?

322
00:23:28.760 --> 00:23:29.490
She is...

323
00:23:30.500 --> 00:23:34.100
a monster in the form of a little girl!

324
00:23:36.790 --> 00:23:40.130
Episode 01
The Devil of the Rhine

325
00:23:36.790 --> 00:23:40.130
This program is fiction.
All persons. groups. places. laws.
and names appearing in it have
no relation to the real world.
